				<li id="16799936" class="cmnt-root" data="0" data-d="1669341055000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578372/Troll's-Hammer" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">24 Nov 2022 20:50</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16799936" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">The Troll&apos;s Hammer colossal weapon deals Physical and Fire damage by default and allows external weapon buffs from spells and weapon greases - it&apos;s weapon art (Troll&apos;s Roar) isn&apos;t great for PvP, however it&apos;s fine for PvE and can be very powerful when synergised with talisman, plus it deals STRIKE type physical damage at 16.0 units and at +25 has a low B (97) STR scaling, a high E (22) DEX scaling and a mid-high D (45) FTH scaling means that if you&apos;re playing a Faith+Strength user you can add a lightning or holy damage buff to it, granting you 3 separate damage types, and then an additional boost in damage from the Strength scaling when wielded 2handed. <br/><br/>The fact this weapon can be buffed means that if you&apos;re primarliy invested in Faith, an Erdtree Seal +10 at 80 Faith will grant it an extra +265 lightning/holy damage (or 229 fire with Blackflame). With Golden Vow and FGMS it can reach an AR value higher than the Giant Crusher or Prelate&apos;s when fully buffed and 2handed (assuming 60str), it&apos;s the next best option to deal Strike damage with huge AR that doesn&apos;t weight more than 20+ units or deal holy damage. Absolute 9.5/10 weapon for a Faith Strength 2hander build.</p>