				<li id="16769480" class="cmnt-root" data="10" data-d="1662515026000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578372/Troll's-Hammer" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">06 Sep 2022 21:43</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16769480" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This is turning out to be a pretty solid weapon for a STR/ Faith hybrid build and one you should seriously consider fully upgrading given it&apos;s one of the few weapons that suit that type of build that get upgraded by regular smithing stones. Other than your Clawmark Seal and maybe a greatshield if you use one of those, you&apos;re going to have a limited number of Somber Ancient stones to fully upgrade your weaponry and a bunch of extra normal ancient smithing stones. Somber weapons with hybrid scaling is going to start outperforming &quot;normal&quot; weapons because we don&apos;t have affinities that tend to handle mixed scaling like that. Quality combines DEX and STR, but there isn&apos;t an equivalent for STR and Faith or DEX and INT.<br/><br/>The Troll&apos;s Hammer is an &quot;extra&quot; weapon you can have available that doesn&apos;t eat up your somber stones, and it does bonk damage for crystalians and other irritating enemies that are weak to it on top of allowing you to buff it with incantations despite doing some non-physical damage, one of the very few weapons that allows that currently.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle=